################################################################################
# MVP 3 — USER (JOB SEEKER) DASHBOARD
# AI-Based Recruitment & Skill-Matching Platform
# Goal: Build the complete User Dashboard with Profile, Resume, Jobs & History
# Reference: Image shows sidebar with Profile, Setting, Job, History, Applied
################################################################################

## PHASE 1: Database Schema — Candidate Profiles & Resumes
[ ] Create `candidate_profiles` table:
    [ ] user_id (FK → users.id, unique)
    [ ] headline (e.g., "Frontend Developer | 3 Years Exp")
    [ ] summary (bio/about text)
    [ ] location (city, country)
    [ ] phone
    [ ] linkedin_url
    [ ] github_url
    [ ] portfolio_url
    [ ] years_of_experience
    [ ] current_salary
    [ ] expected_salary
    [ ] notice_period (in days)
    [ ] avatar_url
    [ ] created_at, updated_at
[ ] Create `candidate_skills` table:
    [ ] id, candidate_profile_id, skill_name, proficiency_level (beginner/intermediate/expert)
[ ] Create `candidate_education` table:
    [ ] id, candidate_profile_id, degree, institution, field_of_study, start_year, end_year, grade
[ ] Create `candidate_experience` table:
    [ ] id, candidate_profile_id, job_title, company, start_date, end_date, is_current, description
[ ] Create `resumes` table:
    [ ] id (UUID), user_id (FK), filename, file_url, file_size
    [ ] ai_extracted_text (TEXT — parsed resume content)
    [ ] ai_skills (JSON array of extracted skills)
    [ ] ai_summary (AI-generated text summary)
    [ ] is_primary (boolean)
    [ ] uploaded_at
[ ] Create `job_applications` table:
    [ ] id (UUID), user_id (FK), job_id (FK)
    [ ] resume_id (FK), cover_letter
    [ ] status (ENUM: 'applied', 'screening', 'shortlisted', 'interview', 'rejected', 'offered')
    [ ] ai_match_score (decimal 0-100)
    [ ] applied_at, updated_at
[ ] Run DB migrations

## PHASE 2: Backend — User Profile APIs
[ ] GET /api/user/profile → return current user's profile
[ ] POST /api/user/profile → create profile (first-time setup)
[ ] PUT /api/user/profile → update profile details
[ ] PUT /api/user/profile/avatar → upload avatar image (multipart/form-data)
[ ] POST /api/user/profile/skills → add skill
[ ] DELETE /api/user/profile/skills/:id → remove skill
[ ] POST /api/user/profile/education → add education entry
[ ] PUT /api/user/profile/education/:id → update education
[ ] DELETE /api/user/profile/education/:id → remove education
[ ] POST /api/user/profile/experience → add work experience
[ ] PUT /api/user/profile/experience/:id → update experience
[ ] DELETE /api/user/profile/experience/:id → remove experience
[ ] GET /api/user/settings → return account settings
[ ] PUT /api/user/settings → update settings (email notifications, privacy, etc.)
[ ] PUT /api/user/settings/password → change password (verify old password first)

## PHASE 3: Backend — Resume APIs
[ ] POST /api/user/resumes → upload resume PDF/DOCX (multipart)
    [ ] Validate: file type (pdf/docx only), size (max 5MB)
    [ ] Save file to cloud storage (AWS S3 / Cloudinary / Firebase Storage)
    [ ] Store metadata in DB
    [ ] Queue AI parsing job (async)
    [ ] Return: { resume: {...}, message: "Resume uploaded. AI analysis in progress." }
[ ] GET /api/user/resumes → list all uploaded resumes
[ ] DELETE /api/user/resumes/:id → delete a resume
[ ] PUT /api/user/resumes/:id/set-primary → set as primary resume
[ ] GET /api/user/resumes/:id/analysis → return AI analysis results for a resume

## PHASE 4: Backend — Job Browse & Application APIs  
[ ] GET /api/jobs → list published jobs with pagination + filters:
    [ ] Query params: keyword, location, salary_min, salary_max, job_type, experience_level, page, limit
    [ ] If user is authenticated, include ai_match_score per job
[ ] GET /api/jobs/:id → get single job details
[ ] POST /api/jobs/:id/apply → apply for a job (authenticated user only)
    [ ] Validate: user has uploaded at least one resume
    [ ] Create application record
    [ ] Trigger AI matching score computation (async)
    [ ] Send confirmation email (optional)
[ ] GET /api/user/applications → list all applications by the logged-in user
    [ ] Include job title, company, status, match score, applied_at
[ ] GET /api/user/applications/:id → get single application detail

