[ ] Job detail view (modal or nested route):
    [ ] Full job description
    [ ] Required skills list
    [ ] Company info
    [ ] AI Match breakdown (which skills match, which are missing)
    [ ] "Apply Now" button → apply flow (select resume + write cover letter)
    [ ] Application confirmation modal

## PHASE 9: Frontend — Applied Section (/dashboard/applied)
[ ] Application history table:
    [ ] Columns: Job Title, Company, Applied Date, Status, AI Match Score, Actions
    [ ] Status badge colors: applied (blue), screening (orange), shortlisted (green), rejected (red)
    [ ] "View Details" → shows full application + job info
    [ ] "Withdraw" button (if status is 'applied')
[ ] Status timeline view per application (step tracker)

## PHASE 10: Frontend — History Section (/dashboard/history)
[ ] "Jobs Viewed" list with timestamps
[ ] "Saved Jobs" list
[ ] Account activity log (profile updates, resume uploads, applications)

## PHASE 11: Frontend — Settings Section (/dashboard/settings)
[ ] Account settings form:
    [ ] Change email
    [ ] Change password (old + new + confirm)
    [ ] Email notification preferences (checkboxes):
        [ ] New job matches
        [ ] Application status updates
        [ ] Weekly digest
    [ ] Privacy settings:
        [ ] Profile visibility toggle (public / private)
[ ] Danger zone:
    [ ] "Delete Account" button (with confirmation dialog)

## DELIVERABLES / ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA
[ ] User can view and edit their profile from the dashboard
[ ] User can upload a resume (PDF/DOCX) and see AI analysis results
[ ] User can browse jobs with filters and search
[ ] "Apply" button requires resume to be uploaded
[ ] Applied jobs are listed with live status tracking
[ ] AI Match Score appears on job cards (after resume upload + AI processing)
[ ] All dashboard sections are responsive on mobile and tablet
